Bank of China, the nation’s second- biggest lender, may raise as much as $8 billion in a Hong Kong initial public offering in June after shelving plans for a simultaneous sale in Shanghai, Bloomberg News reported.

Bank of China is trying to keep its overseas IPO plan on track to tap increasing appetite for Asian bank shares, which has seen the Morgan Stanley Capital International Index of Asian financial stocks excluding Japan rise 17 percent in the past 12 months.

